INSERT INTO `ipqu_posts` VALUES (307, 2, '2018-09-29 17:01:48', '2018-09-29 17:01:48', 'This privacy policy sets out how ipQuants AG uses and protects any information that you give ipQuants when you use this website.\r\n\r\nipQuants is committed to ensuring that your privacy is protected. Should we ask you to provide certain information by which you can be identified when using this website, then you can be assured that it will only be used in accordance with this privacy statement.\r\n\r\nipQuants may change this policy from time to time by updating this page. You should check this page from time to time to ensure that you are happy with any changes. This policy is effective from March 1st, 2016 and was latest updated September 29th, 2018.\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>What information do we collect</dt>\r\n</dl>\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>We may collect the following information:</dt>\r\n 	<dt></dt>\r\n</dl>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>E-mail address to create an account.  This could be a company generic email or your personal email, depending on your organisations preferences. For security purposes, for your safety and ipQuants safety, we store the IP address of all logged in devices.</li>\r\n 	<li>Company contact information including phone numbers for billing purposes.</li>\r\n 	<li>other information relevant to customer offers and surveys that we might do occasionally</li>\r\n 	<li>Information collection by our partners and vendors. Some content or applications on our website is served by third parties, including companies that help us run and optimize our website and process invoices.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>What we do with the information we collect</dt>\r\n 	<dd>We require this information to understand your needs and provide you with a better product and service. Specifically, we collect this information for, among others, the following reasons:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Internal record keeping for billing and platform access purposes.</li>\r\n 	<li>If you have signed up for our newsletters, we may use your email to periodically send promotional emails about new products, special offers or industry relevant news and insights to you.</li>\r\n 	<li>personalize ipQuants products and services; for future product development; newsletter; for routine business purposes; to fulfill our legal, or contractual obligations; and to fulfill any other purpose for which you provide information.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe may disclose information to our business partners and vendors who assist ipQuants in performing these functions. We do not sell or provide personal information that we collect to third parties so that they can try to sell you other products or for other direct marketing purposes.\r\n\r\n<i>Children’s Privacy.</i> Our website is not designed for children under 16 years of age. If you believe we might have any information from or about a child under 16, please contact us at cs@ipQuants.com so that we may delete any such information we unknowingly obtained.</dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>Do Not Track.</dt>\r\n 	<dd>ipQuants respects our visitors’ privacy choices. ipQuants’ website does not recognize browser “do not track” settings, but visitors can disable cookies through their browser settings—check your browser’s help files or consider visiting a third-party website such such as http://www.allaboutcookies.org. Disabling cookies may impede website functionality.</dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>Security</dt>\r\n 	<dd>We take data security very seriously, and take reasonable and appropriate precautions to protect the personal information we collect from unauthorized use or disclosure. That said, no data security system can guarantee 100% security, and ipQuants disclaims any express or implied guarantee that data you provide to ipQuants will never be compromised.</dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>How we use cookies</dt>\r\n 	<dd>Like other website, we also use cookies when you access our website. A cookie is a small file which asks permission to be placed on your computer’s hard drive. Once you agree, the file is added and the cookie helps analyse web traffic or lets you know when you visit a particular site. Cookies allow web applications to respond to you as an individual.\r\n\r\nWe use traffic log cookies to identify which pages are being used. This helps us analyse data about web page traffic and improve our website in order to tailor it to customer needs. We only use this information for statistical analysis purposes and then the data is removed from the system.\r\n\r\nOverall, cookies help us provide you with a better website, by enabling us to monitor which pages you find useful and which you do not. A cookie in no way gives us access to your computer or any information about you, other than the data you choose to share with us.\r\n\r\nYou can choose to accept or decline cookies. Most web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies if you prefer. This may prevent you from taking full advantage of the website.</dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>Links to other websites</dt>\r\n 	<dd>Our website contains links to other websites of interest. However, once you have used these links to leave the ipQuants site, you acknowledge that ipQuants does not have any control over that other website. Therefore, we cannot be responsible for the protection and privacy of any information which you provide whilst visiting such sites and such sites are not governed by this privacy policy.</dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>Controlling your personal information</dt>\r\n 	<dd>You may choose to restrict the collection or use of your personal information in the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>if you have previously agreed to us using your personal information for direct marketing purposes, you may change your mind at any time by writing to or emailing us at cs@ipQuants.com. We will then delete or update your data as per your instructions.</li>\r\n 	<li>We will not sell, distribute or lease your personal information, if we have any, to third parties unless we have your permission or are required by law to do so.</li>\r\n 	<li>If you believe that any information we are holding on you is incorrect or incomplete, please write to or email us as soon as possible, at the above address. We will promptly delete or correct any information found to be incorrect.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt>Questions</dt>\r\n 	<dd>If you have any other questions in view of our privacy policy, please contact us under cs@ipQuants.com.</dd>\r\n</dl>', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '131-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-29 17:01:48', '2018-09-29 17:01:48', '', 131, 'https://ipquants.com/131-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
